title: testscript.py throws "terminate called after throwing an instance of 'Xbyak::Error' what():  can't alloc"
body:
After installing as recommended, I get the above error when it starts training after merging datasets. There also appears to be a tensorflow error earlier in the process that didn't halt the script, but it had run through training at least once successfully. I installed via these commands:
```
git clone https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut.git
cd DeepLabCut/conda-environments/
conda env create -f DLC-CPU.yaml
conda activate DLC-CPU
pip install --upgrade deeplabcut
conda install -y -c conda-forge ffmpeg
cd ../examples/
```
Full error log at the bottom.
